<p>When implementing a Windows Service derived from <code>ServiceBase</code>, is it necessary to explicitly call base class methods such as <code>OnSessionChange(...)</code>, <code>OnStart(...)</code>, <code>OnStop()</code> or <code>Dispose(disposing)</code> inside the equivalent overridden methods? Like:</p>  <pre><code>protected override void OnShutdown() {     // our own logic     base.OnShutdown(); // &lt;- is this call necessary? for base.Dispose(...)? others? } </code></pre>  <p>I presume it should not be necessary but needed to be sure about it; especially the <code>Dispose</code> method.</p>